<dl id="n10099f"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n10" href="#n10099f">N10 (VI.B.16)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n10all.htm#n10099f"> 99(f)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Whitlaw &amp; Walsh / Hist. of Dublin / 1818</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><b>By the Way <font color="green">[&hellip;]</font> Graveyard Loot. <font color="green">[&hellip;]</font></b> There is a story told in <mark>Whitlaw&apos;s and Walsh&apos;s <cite>History of Dublin</cite> (1818)</mark> of a Jew having visited a Christian friend in the neighbourhood of Ballybough. <font color="green">[&hellip;]</font> Picture the feelings of the poor man when, upon closer examination <font color="green">[of a stone near the fireplace]</font> he found it bore an inscription in Hebrew, intimating that his own father was buried beneath it! <small> <a name="FJ1may24" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#FJ1may24"><cite title="source">Freeman's Journal</cite></a> (1 May 1924) 8/5</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: See also: sourced index at <a name="n35273e" href="n35all.htm#n35273e">N35 (VI.B.24):273(e)</a> <i>et seq</i>. </mm> </dd></dl>
